Ladies to Dante. Art thou the man who oft hath been inclined

To sing of Her, addressing us alone?

His voice and thine, indeed, are like in tone, And yet thy visage seems of different kind. Alas! why weepest thou, so unresigned

That thou wouldst kindle pity in a stone?

Oh! hast thou listened to her piteous moan, Who canst not now conceal thy sorrowing mind?
